
JavaScript:

    - A loosely-typed scripting language.
    - This executes on the browser.
    - This turns HTML web pages into interactive web pages.
    - NodeJS provides runtime environment to JavaScript.

NodeJS:

    - NodeJS is JavaScript Server Side Framework.
    - Allows to work with File System, Database, Network and Endpoints.
    - NodeJS provides runtime environment to JavaScript.

How to include JavaScript into HTML?

    - Internal/Ebedded JavaScript
    - External JavaScript
    - Inline JavaScript

HTML - What content has to be displayed. (Content)
CSS - How the content has to be displayed. (Presentation)
JavaScript - What actions needs to be taken on events. (Action)

ctrl + ` : To show/hide the VS terminal

------------------------

JavaScript Data Types:

    - Primitive(Value) Data-Types
        Number, Boolean, String, Null, Undefined
    - Non-Primitive(Reference) Data-Types
        Objects, Arrays, Date

------------------------

JavaScript Operators:

    - Assignment Operators (=)
    - Comparison Operators (>, <, >=, <=, ==, !=)
    - Arithmetic Operators (+, -, *, /)
    - Logical Operators (&&, ||, !)
    - Ternary/Conditional Operators (?)

-------------------------

Conditions:

    - If..else
    - If.. else if.. else
    - Nested If..else
    - switch case

--------------------------

Functions:

    - Simple Function
    - Function with Parameters
    - Function with Parameters and Return Statement
    - Function Expression
    - Annonymous Function
    - Arrow Function

----------------------------

JavaScript Objects:

    1. Object Literal
    2. Object Constructor

---------------------------

























